parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and jerking can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips when the car is warm and the transmission fluid is warm/hot
the vehicle jerks forward when pressing the brakes
the vehicle jerks and would not accelerate for a few seconds
the transmission would not shift properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the digital cluster can cause the vehicle to display incorrect or no information, making it difficult for the driver to monitor the vehicle's performance, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge would not function properly
the speedometer needle would not move and stayed below zero
the digital cluster would fade out to a blank screen
the digital cluster would not make any warning sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause inaccurate readings of fuel levels, speed, and other vital vehicle information, which can lead to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Fuel gauge and other components are not accurate
